  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR Call  1- Promoting the agenda of Youth, Women And PWDs in Election 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The responsiveness of the Members of Parliament towards the electorates will be
improved Electorates will vote on issues and not personality Disability friendly voting
centers will be set up for elections 2016 by the EC. Concerns of youth women, PWDs, and
the aged be properly captured and documented. Reduced spoilt/invalid votes</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project shall make use of 301 volunteers who will all come from our member groups. The civic union concept is founded on the spirit of volunteerism which has sustained UCSOND for over a decade. They all reside in those electoral areas and, therefore, they will not require transportation in doing the work. Most of these volunteers have already benefited from our various capacity building workshops and therefore require less resources to do effective job. Also, due to the high civic responsibility of the volunteers, any capacity given to them will be made available even if the project is ended ensuring sustainability of our intervention. The project will be very efficient in the use of resources since the use of residents will make us reach more people with less resources The project will demand a lot of travel during implementation. UCSOND seeks to cut down cost drastically by mostly using normal public transport fares instead of the use of organisation&#x2019;s car or hired vehicle which has high cost implication because of high cost of fuel. Our Executive Committee members per the policy of the organisation are to travel by normal public transport. Our transport policy also allows staff to use public transport for
some travels.</narrative>
  </description>
